				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \begin{array}{l}\  Sensitivity=\frac{TP}{\ TP+FN}\hfill \\ {} Specificity=\frac{TN}{\ TN+FP},\hfill \end{array} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M2"><mml:mtable columnalign="left"><mml:mtr columnalign="left"><mml:mtd columnalign="left"><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">Sensitivity</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>P</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mi>F</mml:mi><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac></mml:mtd></mml:mtr><mml:mtr columnalign="left"><mml:mtd columnalign="left"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">Specificity</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mi>N</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mi>F</mml:mi><mml:mi>P</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mtext>,</mml:mtext></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="13059_2016_888_Article_Equa.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where true positives (TP) are the number of low quality cells and true negatives (TN) are the number of high quality cells. This defines sensitivity as the proportion of correctly classified low quality cells, and specificity as the proportion of correctly identified high quality cells.</p>
      <p>Total accuracy was calculated as follows: <inline-formula id="IEq1"><alternatives><tex-math id="M3">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
